{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 19:53:25.013359", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nSummary\\n- Anomaly detected: Host pc_0_0 cannot reach its default gateway (10.0.0.1) or remote host pc_0_1. Host pc_0_1 can reach its gateway (10.0.1.1).\\n- Control plane (BGP) is healthy across all routers.\\n- Fault localized to leaf_router_0_0’s configuration and FIB: a misconfigured static blackhole for 10.0.0.0/30 is installed and advertised, causing blackholing of traffic to both the gateway and host addresses in that range.\\n- Root cause: Misconfiguration on leaf_router_0_0 (static blackhole and BGP advertisement of 10.0.0.0/30) overriding the connected host subnet for the most specific addresses.\\n\\nDetailed Findings\\n\\n1) Reachability and host-facing anomalies\\n- pc_0_0 -> default gateway 10.0.0.1: 100% loss.\\n  Evidence: pc_0_0 ping 10.0.0.1: 2 tx, 0 rx.\\n- leaf_router_0_0 -> host 10.0.0.2: 100% loss.\\n  Evidence: leaf_router_0_0 ping 10.0.0.2: 2 tx, 0 rx.\\n- pc_0_1 -> default gateway 10.0.1.1: OK.\\n  Evidence: 0% loss, sub-ms RTT.\\n\\nL2/ARP looks nominal:\\n- pc_0_0 ARP entry for 10.0.0.1 present: 10.0.0.1 lladdr 92:bc:b5:a1:b6:c6 (router MAC), state DELAY.\\n- leaf_router_0_0 ARP entry for 10.0.0.2 present: 10.0.0.2 lladdr c2:ff:fe:d6:ca:1b, state STALE.\\n- leaf_router_0_0 eth4 counters show RX>0, TX low; suggests router receives frames from host but does not send replies.\\n\\nInterpretation: Layer-2 adjacency exists; failure is at L3 forwarding/response on leaf_router_0_0.\\n\\n2) Control-plane health (BGP)\\n- All BGP sessions on leaves, spines, and super-spine are Established, with expected prefixes exchanged.\\n  Evidence: show ip bgp summary on leaf_router_0_0, leaf_router_0_1, spine_router_0_0, spine_router_0_1, super_spine_router_0 show neighbors up and prefixes received/sent.\\n\\n3) Data-plane routing on leaf_router_0_0\\n- leaf_router_0_0 routing table includes a connected 10.0.0.0/24 on eth4 (expected) but also a more-specific blackhole route for 10.0.0.0/30:\\n  - “S>* 10.0.0.0/30 unreachable (blackhole)” and “blackhole 10.0.0.0/30 proto static”.\\n- FRR config contains:\\n  - ip route 10.0.0.0/30 Null0\\n  - address-family IPv4: network 10.0.0.0/24 and network 10.0.0.0/30\\n\\nImpact of this misconfiguration:\\n- Because 10.0.0.2 (pc_0_0) and 10.0.0.1 (leaf default gateway) both lie within 10.0.0.0/30, the more-specific blackhole route takes precedence over the connected /24 when the router needs to forward to 10.0.0.2 or reply to it. Thus:\\n  - leaf_router_0_0 drops packets destined to 10.0.0.2 (no ARP, no forwarding).\\n  - ICMP echo replies from leaf_router_0_0 to pc_0_0 are locally discarded due to the /30 blackhole, causing pc_0_0’s ping to 10.0.0.1 to fail despite L2 adjacency.\\n- The /30 is also advertised via BGP, so remote nodes may prefer the /30 for 10.0.0.0–10.0.0.3 and forward toward leaf_router_0_0, which then blackholes them, breaking any inter-subnet reachability to 10.0.0.1/10.0.0.2.\\n\\n4) Scope and localization\\n- Affects only the leaf 0_0 host subnet 10.0.0.0/24 for addresses within 10.0.0.0/30 (notably 10.0.0.1 gateway and 10.0.0.2 host). Leaf 0_1 and its host 10.0.1.0/24 operate normally.\\n- Upstream spines and super-spine are functioning correctly; BGP is stable; the problem is localized to the host-facing routing on leaf_router_0_0.\\n\\nRoot Cause\\n- Misconfiguration on leaf_router_0_0: a static blackhole route for 10.0.0.0/30 and its advertisement via BGP. This more-specific discard route supersedes the connected /24 for key addresses, causing packet drops and breaking host-gateway communication for pc_0_0.\\n\\nKey Evidence Excerpts\\n- leaf_router_0_0 FRR running-config:\\n  - ip route 10.0.0.0/30 Null0\\n  - address-family ipv4 unicast: network 10.0.0.0/24 and network 10.0.0.0/30\\n- leaf_router_0_0 routing table:\\n  - blackhole 10.0.0.0/30 proto static metric 20\\n  - 10.0.0.0/24 dev eth4 proto kernel scope link src 10.0.0.1\\n- leaf_router_0_0 cannot ping 10.0.0.2; pc_0_0 cannot ping 10.0.0.1 (100% loss in both cases), while pc_0_1 <-> 10.0.1.1 is healthy.\\n- BGP summaries show all sessions Established and prefixes exchanged as expected (no control-plane fault).\\n\\nConclusion\\n- The network is otherwise healthy in the control plane and core/interconnects, but there is a host-facing data-plane misconfiguration on leaf_router_0_0 introducing a blackhole for 10.0.0.0/30. This is the root cause of pc_0_0’s loss of connectivity to its default gateway and to other subnets., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='a1647914-7819-4a5b-a336-a583cd9eccef'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
